      "Realloc (re-allocation)",
      "\u2022 realloc changes a previous allocation (resizes it)",
      "\u2022 Resizes the previous allocation in place, if possible",
      "\u2022 Can be resized larger, or smaller!",
      "\u2022 If it can\u2019t resize in place, it will create a new allocation and copy data",
      "for you",
      "\u2022 Essentially does:",
      "\u2022 new_allocation = malloc(new_size)",
      "\u2022 memcpy(new_allocation, old_allocation, new_size)",
      "\u2022 returns NULL if the memory could not be allocated",
      "void *realloc(void *ptr, size_t size)"
    ]
  },
