    "lines": [
      "Dynamic Memory Deallocation",
      "\u2022 To reap/release/free any dynamically allocated data, use free",
      "\u2022 The passed pointer must point to the first byte of heap-allocated memory",
      "\u2022 i.e., what previously returned by a malloc( ) or calloc( )",
      "\u2022 Free does NOT work on statically or automatically allocated memory!*",
      "\u2022 free(NULL) does nothing (for safety, we\u2019ll talk about it)",
      "\u2022 After freeing a block of memory,",
      "that block of memory can be used",
      "by some future malloc/calloc",
      "\u2022 Enables memory reuse!",
      "void free(void* ptr);",
