    "slide_number": 40,
    "lines": [
      "Dangling Pointers",
      "\u2022 When a pointer points to a memory address that is accessible (non-NULL) but not",
      "valid (unallocated/maintained by someone else) it is said that the pointer is a",
      "dangling pointer",
      "\u2022 Why is this an issue?",
      "\u2022 What would happen if you started to use",
      "a pointer after it has been freed?",
      "\u2022 It could have been allocated to some",
      "other dynamic call!",
      "\u2022 Solution? Use NULL pointers!",
      "\u2022 Recall that (1) any attempt to deference NULL causes a segmentation fault",
      "\u2022 And that (2) free(NULL) does nothing and is safe/ignored",
      "\u2022 You should always NULL a pointer after you have free\u2019d it",
      "\u2022 it\u2019s better to have a segfault than to corrupt memory! (MEMORY ERRORS CAN BE SILENT!)",
      "long* arr = calloc(10*sizeof(long));",
      "if (arr == NULL) return -1;",
      "// .. do something ..",
      "free(arr);",
      "arr = NULL;"
    ]
  },
